Okinawan Cream of Mushroom Soup
  --Kae Izena
  
1 small onion or 3/4 c leeks chopped
1 tbsp vegetable oil
1 tsp salt
1 1/2 c shiitake mushrooms (or use 1/2 c of each of shiitake, enoki, and shemeji mushrooms)
1 tsp grated ginger
2  plain soy milk
1 bay leaf
1 tbsp miso paste

In a large pot stir fry the onion in oil with a dash of salt until soft, ~5-6 min. Add mushrooms and continue sauteing until soft. Add ginger, soy milk, and bay leaf and bring to a simmer. Simmer for 3 min. Turn off heat, remove bay leaf, and stir in miso at the end.
